President Trump began his visit to Paris by meeting with staff and Bastille Day participants at the U.S. Embassy. He praised the bravery and heroism of U.S. and French soldiers during World War I and II. He was joined by three American veterans of D-Day. Later, Trump and First Lady Melania had an arrival ceremony at Hotel Invalides and visited Les Invalides. Melania visited a hospital while Trump had a bilateral meeting with President Macron, discussing Syria, counterterrorism, trade, and cybersecurity. They held a joint press conference, highlighting the historic relationship between the U.S. and France. The day ended with a private dinner at the Eiffel Tower.